OL,3,CPrime Minister to commit to 2.5% for
OL,4,Cdefence spending within days
OL,6,FOfficials in the Treasury and Downing
OL,7,FStreet are working on the numbers to
OL,8,Fallow the prime minister to make the
OL,9,Fcommitment in the middle of the week.
OL,11,FHitting the 2.5% target would cost an
OL,12,Fadditional #6bn a year, according to
OL,13,Fthe Institute for Fiscal Studies.
OL,15,FIt would heap even more pressure on
OL,16,Fthe chancellor to squeeze the spending
OL,17,Fof other departments and extract as
OL,18,Fmuch as possible from planned radical
OL,19,Fwelfare reform.
