OL,3,CPrime Minister to commit to 2.5% for
OL,4,Cdefence spending within days
OL,6,FStill to be decided, I am told, is
OL,7,Fwhether to ramp up to 2.5% immediately
OL,8,For do it gradually over two-to-four
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,FThe concern in the Treasury is that
OL,12,Framping up quickly would lead to waste
OL,13,Fand equipment inflation.
OL,15,FHowever there is almost no difference
OL,16,Fto whether the fiscal rules are met in
OL,17,Fthe choice between increasing spend
OL,18,Fover a year or four years.
OL,20,FPressures are growing for even greater
OL,21,Fdefence spending.
