OL,3,CPrime Minister to commit to 2.5% for
OL,4,Cdefence spending within days
OL,6,FIn the spring NATO members will decide
OL,7,Fon a new minimum spending threshold,
OL,8,Fwhich is widely expected to be 3%.
OL,10,FAnd in coming weeks a radical new
OL,11,Fapproach to defending the nation will
OL,12,Fbe published in the form of the
OL,13,FStrategic Defence Review, commissioned
OL,14,Fby the government.
OL,16,FThe UK government is also taking a
OL,17,Fkeen interest in plans to raise E100bn
OL,18,Facross Europe from the creation of a
OL,19,Fso-called re-armament bank, a project
OL,20,Fpromoted by the Polish foreign
OL,21,Fminister Radek Sikorski.
